                        <interp inst="t18760403-name-373" type="given" value="CHARLES"></interp>CHARLES CHEESEMAN</persName>
                  </hi>. I live at 7, Clyde Terrace, Forest Hill—on 29th January, I was in the taproom of the Bird-in-Hand public-house—to the best of my belief the prisoner is the man I saw there—it was as near as I can recollect, about 8.45 when I went in—he had a bundle of clothes with him, and he offered me this coat (<hi rend="italic">produced</hi>) for sale which I bought for 4<hi rend="italic">s</hi>. 6<hi rend="italic">d</hi>.—on the following Monday, in consequence of a communication I gave the coat up to the police.</p>
